passages.text:
{"character": "Narration"}
You rush into your 15-466 class, panting. The bus had arrived 20 minutes late and caused you to be, well, 20 minutes late. You can feel Jim's eyes staring into your soul as you take your seat in the back of the class.
[[Next->Story 1]]

{"character": "Narration"}
As you catch your breath and settle into your seat, your eyes dart up to the chalkboard. The agenda had only one item on it and as your mind processes the words, you feel your heart sink with dread.
[[Next->Story 2]]

{"character": "Jim"}
Yes, today is Prototype Day! I sure hope you have all your prototypes ready to go!
[[Next->Story 3]]

{"character": "Narration"}
Your mind flashes back to the night before. How you decided to spend just another hour making dinner. How you stayed up till 5am watching League. And now you're showing up to class without a prototype to share.
[[Next->Story 4]]

{"character": "Narration"}
As you pray with all your heart to not be the next one chosen, Jim looks directly at you and smiles.
[[Next->Story 5]]

{"character": "Narrator", "relationship": -10}
Quickly pulling up Flappy Bird on your computer, you pretend that you have a working prototype and present it to the class. Your classmates immediately recognize that you are a cheater and a bad liar and you shamefully are removed from the class.
[[Next->Check Node]]

{"character": "Narrator", "relationship": 10}
You tell the rest of class about your life story, adding in a few embellishments for bonus sympathy points. Jim grunts in disappointment and calls on the next person. Your grade may haved suffered, but at least your reputation remains untarnished.
[[Next->Check Node]]

{"character": "Narrator", "relationship": -10}
You stand there, saying nothing, and hoping that things will work out. Unfortunately... it did not. Jim sends you home to reflect on your actions.
[[Next->Check Node]]

{"character": "Narrator", "relationship": -10}
You stumble over yourself, trying to say some words but only spitting out an incoherent mess. The class looks at you in confusion, and Jim's facial expression can only be described with immense disappointment. You leave the classroom in distress.
[[Next->Check Node]]
